******Exploratory Data Analysis for Eye Tracking Dyslexia Dataset***
We perfomed an exploratory data analysis to understand the dataset prior to training an eye tracking dyslexia model.
These visualizations cover univariate distributions, bivariate relationships, time‑series trends across blocks and aggregated performance metrics.
These are the 25 EDA visualisations;
1.Bar plot of Gender distribution.
2.Bar plot of Nativelang distribution (Yes/No).
3.Bar plot of Otherlang distribution (Yes/No).
4.Histogram of Age distribution.
5.Bar plot of Dyslexia counts.
6.Boxplot of Age by Dyslexia.
7.Stacked bar of Gender by Dyslexia.
8.Stacked bar of Nativelang by Dyslexia.
9.Stacked bar of Otherlang by Dyslexia.
10.Line plot of mean Accuracy across blocks for Dyslexia groups.
11.Line plot of mean Missrate across blocks for Dyslexia groups.
12.Line plot of mean Hits across blocks for Dyslexia groups.
13.Line plot of mean Clicks across blocks for Dyslexia groups.
14.Heatmap of correlation between Accuracy across blocks.
15.Boxplot of overall mean Accuracy per person by Dyslexia.
16.Boxplot of overall mean Missrate per person by Dyslexia.
17.Boxplot of overall mean Hits per person by Dyslexia.
18.Boxplot of overall mean Clicks per person by Dyslexia.
19.Scatter plot of Age vs overall mean Accuracy, colored by Dyslexia.
20.Pairplot of demographic variables (Gender, Nativelang, Otherlang, Age) with hue=Dyslexia.
21.Violin plot of Age by Dyslexia.
22.Count plot of Dyslexia by Gender and Native Language.
23.Distribution of total Clicks (sum across blocks) by Dyslexia (histogram or boxplot).
24.Distribution of total Hits (sum across blocks) by Dyslexia.
25.Distribution of total Misses (sum across blocks) by Dyslexia.